<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3152801" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="CHG" oldref="9"><variable id="floating_toolbar"><link href="text/shared/guide/floating_toolbar.xhp" name="Using Floating Toolbars">Using Toolbars</link>
</variable></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3143267" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="7">Use the <emph>Insert</emph> icon to insert objects into a text document. Click the arrow next to this icon to open a toolbar containing further icons.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3155450" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="8">You now have a choice: either click the icon that you want to activate, or seize the toolbar by its title bar and drag it while holding down the mouse button. </paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN106E9" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">To Make a Toolbar a Floating Toolbar</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN106D9" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Do one of the following:</paragraph>
<list type="unordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN106EF" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG">Click in an empty part of the toolbar, and drag the toolbar into the document.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN106F3" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG">Double-click in an empty part of the toolbar.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN106F2" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">To Reattach a Floating Toolbar</paragraph>
<list type="unordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN106F7" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Drag the title bar of the toolbar to an edge of the document window.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
